##Dictation | Germany, where goods are seized everywhere, feels like a stroke of luck..

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

I specifically asked a few Germans not to be rash and not to wear a mask, but rather to look at the vaccination guidelines and decide that they didn't need one. Germany has the advantage of relying heavily on systematicity, but if a link in the system breaks, its overall inflexibility becomes apparent.

Oral | KZ

Organize East Kim Hee

As a Chinese, I never imagined that I would be in the midst of a massive new crown disease outbreak in Germany, and in the worst part of the country.

I am from Ningbo and have been in Germany for four years. I live with my wife in Shanghai in a small town on the edge of Cologne. Cologne is located in Nordrhein-Westfalen, Germany's most affected North Rhine-Westphalia state, known as Nordrhein-Westfalen. It is a federal state of more than 18 million people, a number that does not appeal to the Chinese but is Germany's most populous. Heinsberg, North Rhine Westphalia, is the site of the worst outbreak in Germany. I live in a town only forty minutes from the Heinsberg.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Most diagnosed in Germany -- Heinsberg.

As of March 13,3,074 cases had been confirmed in Germany, of which 1,221 were in Heinsberg, accounting for 525. The HEINSBERG has a population of just over two hundred and fifty thousand. There have been six deaths in Germany, most of them in North Rhine-westphalia. Now the data in Germany is changing very fast, for example, in the district where I live, 10 cases are confirmed in the morning, 2 hours later, 13 cases..

My daily work is engaged in import and export trade, usually the basic bus to and from work, but at present can only choose to stay at home.

The Aloof Germans, too, were taken in

I didn't go home for the Spring Festival this year. So the news of the NCP outbreak was also picked up through media reports and social networks. For me who lived through SARS in Beijing, I was very sensitive to this kind of epidemic. Therefore, I very early remind the domestic family to be vigilant, do not go out easily, not careless.

The German side of the report is very detached, initially felt that the outbreak occurred in China, far away from us. The Germans are more concerned that Turkey has abandoned the EU and allowed 100,000 refugees to flood the Greek border. At the same time, in European countries, to achieve the closure of the country is unthinkable, the law and practical operation is almost impossible, so some people's attitude to China's epidemic is also in the "appalling" with curiosity. When I talk to the Germans around me, they can be a little condescending, even if they're careful. Now, however, the media's attitude is different.

There have been two high tides of the German epidemic. The first was in January this year, when a Chinese employee of a German company in the state of Bayern came to China on a short business trip. He returned to China with a fever and was diagnosed. At the same time that the news reached the German parent company, it happened that the German employees who had contact here also started to have a fever. After a check, they were diagnosed. Then the company and its surrounding contacts began to be quarantined. The employees and their families continued to be diagnosed. Fortunately, all the infected people were suffering from mild illness, ended up leaving the hospital. Germany has now recovered 27 cases, most of them in that time period. This process, on the one hand, shows that Germany began to follow early, appropriate measures, but also seems to give the public a "big deal is not the cause of flu" impression.

What really makes Germans nervous is this week, the second climax. Around late February, a couple from Heinsberg returned from Italy, just in time for the North Wales Carnival, and after the usual eating and drinking, the man was admitted to the hospital, where he was diagnosed, along with his wife, although the woman's symptoms are less severe. As a result, they took part in the Heinsberg, where infected people in contact with the couple continued to spread to and beyond North Rhine Westphalia.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In this year's carnival, the German "new coronaviruses" into a float, did not expect shortly after his own country was also hit

To the dismay of the Chinese, the local government decided last weekend to allow 54,000 fans to enter the Mönchengladbach and Dortmund football game in North Rhine Westphalia, urging only 550 fans from the Heinsberg to cancel their tickets.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The problem is, that course is only 10 kilometers from the Heinsberg! It's been a no-crowd week, but fans are still flocking out of the stadium in droves. There is a detail that the government needs to hear from all the parties involved in making such a big decision, such as the organizers who said they would go bankrupt because the insurance company would not pay the force majeure, so they would end up with the greatest common denominator.

Germans just don't wear masks

As a Chinese, Wuhan City began to close, my first feeling is to buy masks, but something on the delay of a day, the pharmacy clerk said the first day sold out.

Previously, the supermarket here because of Chinese relations, the first out of the supply is rice, then is disinfectant.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The supermarket is out of rice

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Limit the purchase of disinfectants

Now eliminate disinfectant "forever" out of stock, occasionally appear flour, toilet paper out of stock, but every few days will be replaced. Throughout Germany there have been no problems with supplies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
To what extent do Germans listen to the state of mind? At a rally of fewer than 20 people last week, people got up close and personal, not one of them wore a mask! But every ten minutes or so will pass disinfectant hand clean, because the government said that the mask does not work, washing hands is the most important! Now some pharmacies have been licensed to make their own disinfectant in limited quantities per person.

The word "mask" has almost become a nightmare for Chinese Germans! In Europe, in general, masks are worn only when one is sick and afraid of passing them on to others. Moreover, at least so far, no medical expert has come forward to say that universal masks are of particular help in preventing epidemics. I specifically asked several Germans, it's not that they're reckless and don't wear masks, it's that they don't wear them because they think they don't need to after reading the vaccination guidelines. If you go out and wear a mask, you're telling people to stay away from me, that I'm sick and that I'm Chinese. As a result, most people still do not wear masks on the streets of Germany.

I'm feeling a little scared..

My Wife, who works for the European arm of a public company in the United States, has been changing her boss's demands on her work day by day this week. Today's update: You don't need to take time off to work from home.

Germany early announcement, fever do not go directly to the hospital, but call the hotline, will come to deal with. Does the hot line work? I haven't tried it yet. I hope I don't have to find out if it works.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The test is up to the doctor, and although the German Insurance Company pays for the treatment, because health insurance is compulsory in Germany, all expenses are paid out of pocket once the need is identified. The problem people have is that if you feel the need to take a test and the doctor doesn't feel the need, the cost is high. Germany now tends to medical treatment of old age or basic disease and other high-risk groups, you do not meet the above conditions, presumably agree with you to test the probability is low, because doctors believe that if you are physically strong, even if it will heal.

I'm very worried right now. Germany's strategy, first and foremost, is to try to slow the spread and to shift the focus of protection to high-risk populations. Although Germany has managed to beat Italy by almost a month, that advantage is now gone. The colleague of my wife's company, took a leave of absence to fly to Italy to see her husband yesterday, this is unimaginable in China..

Yesterday I got information from a doctor's acquaintance that the emergency room doctors at his hospital were working in "nude" and that the state was not in a position to provide protective equipment. The lack of medical protective equipment is global and can not be solved in reality. She was worried that she would soon see a large number of German doctors quarantined.

I read about the seizure of Swiss masks in Germany. On Wednesday, the day before the incident, Germany had issued a ban on all exports of medical supplies, and Switzerland was caught in the crossfire. In normal times, it was unkind, but when everyone wanted to protect themselves, Germany had the audacity to do it.

Germany has the advantage of relying heavily on systematicity, but if a link in the system breaks, its overall inflexibility becomes apparent. A surgical mask, rather than a national mask, would be the fate of Germany, whose trains are now on a high speed collision course.
